</p>
<p>
  Given the clear differences, I wanted to have a look at what factors in particular might be responsible for creating this health inequality. The absolute range in the chart below is the difference in values between the most and least deprived. Basically, the further the circles are from the zero axis then the greater the gap and circles on the right of the axis indicate the problem being greater for the most deprived whilst circles on the left indicate the problem being greater for the least deprived:
